# Project: <PROJECT-NAME>

This file is a **Binding**: it mandates and routes. It carries no reusable knowledge.
Every substantive standard lives in the skill or doc it points to.

## Skill routing

Use the skill for the task — do not improvise what a skill already knows.

| Task | Skill |
|------|-------|
| Python code structure (models/adapters/services/entrypoints, SOLID, CI) | **meaningfy-engineering:cosmic-python** |
| System / solution design (C4, ADRs, contracts) | **meaningfy-engineering:architecture** |
| New feature or non-trivial change — explore options first | **superpowers:brainstorming** |
| Feature or bugfix implementation — tests first | **superpowers:test-driven-development** |
| Debugging | **superpowers:systematic-debugging** |
| Plan a Work Shape into a spec | **meaningfy-ai-coding:epic-planning** |
| Spec readiness gate | **meaningfy-ai-coding:clarity-gate** |
| BDD / Gherkin features | **meaningfy-ai-coding:bdd-gherkin** |
| Commits / branches / PRs | **meaningfy-engineering:meaningfy-git-workflow** |
| Pre-PR review | **meaningfy-ai-coding:meaningfy-code-review** |
| Docs and technical writing | **meaningfy-ai-coding:technical-writing** |

If a request conflicts with the above, flag it before proceeding.

## Implementation loop

1. Before editing any symbol, run GitNexus impact analysis; stop and report HIGH/CRITICAL risk.
2. Loop: generate (tests first) → verify (run tests) → integrate (present, get consent).
3. On a design-level failure, fix the spec, not the code (Rule of Divergence).
4. Commit only on explicit developer consent.

## Memory conventions

- `.claude/memory/MEMORY.md` — stable, confirmed patterns (≤200 lines; auto-loaded).
- `.claude/memory/epics/<epic-name>/` — `EPIC.md` + dated task files (read the relevant epic on demand).

